.TH "rvt_qp_valid_operation" 9 "rvt_qp_valid_operation" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rvt_qp_valid_operation \- validate post send wr request
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rvt_qp_valid_operation
.BI "(struct rvt_qp *qp "  ","
.BI "const struct rvt_operation_params *post_parms "  ","
.BI "const struct ib_send_wr *wr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "qp" 12
the qp
.IP "post_parms" 12
the post send table for the driver
.IP "wr" 12
the work request
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The routine validates the operation based on the
validation table an returns the length of the operation
which can extend beyond the ib_send_bw.  Operation
dependent flags key atomic operation validation.

There is an exception for UD qps that validates the pd and
overrides the length to include the additional UD specific
length.

Returns a negative error or the length of the work request
for building the swqe.
